<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-28T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="1380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/767</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-28T11:00:00+02:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1915, 11 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 1, 8 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>707. Turkish authorities have commenced deporting from Aleppo six hundred
                            belligerent subjects including women and children on the ground that
                            certain of these were spreading false reports. My protests unavailing.
                            Minister of War [allowed] only remission of order for women and children
                            still there. Telegram just received from Consul General at Smyrna states
                            that similar measures contemplated there.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>